article.description: — Duke Miles and Nick Stampley scored 20 points apiece as Troy topped Georgia Southern 68-56 on Friday night.
article.headline: Troy defeats Georgia Southern 68-56
article.story: TROY, Ala. -- — Duke Miles and Nick Stampley scored 20 points apiece as Troy topped Georgia Southern 68-56 on Friday night. The 20 points were a season high for Miles, who added eight assists. Stampley also had 11 rebounds. Zay Williams had seven rebounds for Troy (10-9, 4-5 Sun Belt Conference), which won its fourth straight game. Kam Woods, whose 12 points per game entering the matchup led the Trojans, shot only 13% for the game (1 of 8). Eric Boone had 16 points for the Eagles (11-9, 5-6). Kamari Brown added 13 points. Zack Bryant, whose 14 points per game entering the contest led the Eagles, shot only 13% for the game (1 of 8). The Trojans registered their first win in three tries against the Eagles this season. In the most recent matchup, Georgia Southern defeated Troy 63-56 on Jan. 16. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
